# CoNLL-U edition of Heliand, DDD edition v1.1
# - orthography of FORM and LEMMA normalized to match HeliPaD
#   Note that HeliPaD and DDD Heliand go back to different manuscripts, so, sometimes the forms differ in morphology, e.g., regarding the [optional] prefix gi-)
#   Moreover, this means that DDD words are systematically replaced by phonologically/orthographically more modern variants, e.g., thuo > do, uurðun > uurdun.
#   Mapping strategy and original FORM provided as comment
# - HeliPaD XPOS extrapolated from alignment with HeliPaD and majority prediction from DDD features with the following preference
#   DPOS+LPOS+FEATS > DPOS+FEATS > LPOS+FEATS > DPOS+LPOS > DPOS > LPOS
#   [DPOS: DDD POS, LPOS: DDD Lemma POS, FEATS: DDD inflection]
# - UPOS similarly extrapolated from majority prediction:
#   DPOS+LPOS > DPOS > LPOS
# - MISC column contains clause-level syntax annotation, marked at the last word of the clause
# Note that DDD multi-word expressions are separated into individual tokens, with annotations
# The original FORM can (and should) be restored from the first word in the comment, but the current version can be used to train parsers and embeddings

